    "body": "## Summary\n\nThis is a targeted fix for the Hopper-swizzled MXFP4 RHS path. MXFP4/MXFP8 matmul coverage already exists elsewhere; the missing piece here was the Hopper value/scale-swizzled MXFP4 RHS path when the LHS is also microscaled, primarily MXFP8.\n\n- In the regular and persistent matmul kernels, the `SWIZZLE_MX_VALUE == \"HOPPER_VALUE\"` branch now keeps the existing BF16 LHS `tl.dot` path, but uses `tl.dot_scaled` when the LHS has MX scales.\n- The matmul wrapper still rejects unsupported swizzled/non-strided MX scale layouts with non-column-major weights, while allowing plain strided row-major MX weights through the regular path.\n- Hopper opt-flag tuning was narrowed to the heavier MX input + Hopper-swizzled MXFP4 RHS + MX output cases, avoiding the register and shared-memory launch failures exposed by the expanded coverage.\n- The test coverage is in the generic `test_matmul.py::test_op` matrix rather than a bespoke operand-combo test, with skips tightened to represent real architecture limits such as A100 `fp8e4nv` support.\n\n## Testing\n\n- GitHub Actions: https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/actions/runs/25387167488 (all checks passing: pre-commit, macOS build, NVIDIA A100/H100/GB200, AMD gfx90a/gfx942/gfx950)\n- Local: `pre-commit run --files python/triton_kernels/tests/test_matmul.py`\n- Local: `python -m compileall -q python/triton_kernels/tests/test_matmul.py`\n",
    "created_at": "2026-05-04T18:04:10Z",
